-- China to Open 10 Airports This Year as Economy Spurs Air Travel, CAAC Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-08T01:52:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/china-to-open-10-airports-this-year-as-economy-spurs-air-travel-caac-says.html

          
          
             China will open 10 new airports this
year, raising the nationwide tally to 176, as economic growth
spurs travel demand, Liu Shaocheng, director of policy research,
at the Civil Aviation Administration of China, said today at a
conference in Beijing.  
